## 4. Import/Export Conventions

### 4.1 Use Named Exports (Preferred)

**✅ Do:**

```typescript
// Component file
export const MyComponent = () => {
  return <div>My Component</div>;
};

export const MyUtilityComponent = () => {
  return <div>Utility</div>;
};

// Importing
import { MyComponent, MyUtilityComponent } from './MyComponent';
```

### 4.2 Default Exports (Acceptable for Page Components)

```typescript
// Page-level components can use default export
const PayoutsPage = () => {
  return <div>Payouts</div>;
};

export default PayoutsPage;
```

### 4.3 Import Organization

**✅ Do:**

```typescript
// 1. External libraries (React, third-party)
import { useState, useEffect, useCallback } from 'react';
import { useNavigate, useLocation } from 'modules/react-router';
import moment from 'moment-timezone';

// 2. Blade components
import { Box, Button, Text, Card } from '@razorpay/blade/components';

// 3. Internal modules (api, modules, utilities)
import api from 'api/api';
import { useAppSelector } from 'modules/storeHooks';
import { formatDate } from 'modules/util';

// 4. Views and UI components
import { showErrorNotification } from 'views/xtra/ui/Notifications/NotificationsReducer';

// 5. Local imports (types, constants, utils)
import { MyComponentProps } from './types';
import { CONSTANTS } from './constants';
import { helperFunction } from './utils';
```

### 4.4 Avoid Barrel Exports Antipattern

**❌ Don't (in most cases):**

```typescript
// utils/index.ts
export * from './util1';
export * from './util2';
export * from './util3';
```

**✅ Do:**

```typescript
// Import specific utilities
import { specificUtil } from 'modules/util/specificUtil';
import { anotherUtil } from 'modules/util/anotherUtil';
```

