## 5. Blade Design System Usage

### 5.1 Always Use Blade Components

**❌ Don't:**

```typescript
import Button from 'ui/Button'; // Old custom button
import { Link as RouterLink } from 'react-router-dom';
```

**✅ Do:**

```typescript
import { Button, Link } from '@razorpay/blade/components';
import { Link } from 'modules/blade/components'; // Wrapped Blade Link with router
```

### 5.2 Use Blade Spacing and Layout

**❌ Don't:**

```typescript
<Box style={{ margin: '10px', padding: '20px' }}>
  <Button style={{ marginTop: '15px' }}>Click</Button>
</Box>
```

**✅ Do:**

```typescript
<Box padding="spacing.5" margin="spacing.3">
  <Button marginTop="spacing.4">Click</Button>
</Box>

// Responsive spacing
<Box
  padding={{ base: 'spacing.3', m: 'spacing.6' }}
  display="flex"
  flexDirection={{ base: 'column', m: 'row' }}
>
  <Button>Click</Button>
</Box>
```

### 5.3 Check Blade Documentation Before Using

```typescript
// Always fetch component docs from Blade MCP before using
// Example: Before using ActionList, fetch its documentation
// to understand proper props and usage patterns

// Use semantic components
// PasswordInput instead of generic TextInput for passwords
import { PasswordInput } from '@razorpay/blade/components';
```

### 5.4 Minimal Component Configuration

**✅ Do:**

```typescript
// Use minimal props - don't add size, color unless explicitly needed
<Button>Submit</Button>

// Add props only when required
<Button size="large" variant="primary">
  Primary Action
</Button>
```

