## 6. State Management

### 6.1 Use Typed Redux Selectors

**✅ Do:**

```typescript
// modules/storeHooks.ts
import { useSelector, TypedUseSelectorHook } from 'react-redux';
import { RootState } from 'types/rootState';

export const useAppSelector: TypedUseSelectorHook<RootState> = useSelector;

// In component
const user = useAppSelector((state) => state.app.user);
const payouts = useAppSelector((state) => state.payouts.items);
```

### 6.2 Selector Best Practices

**✅ Do:**

```typescript
// Create reusable selectors
const selector = ({ app, payouts }: RootState) => ({
  user: app.user,
  items: payouts.items,
  isLoading: payouts.isLoading,
});

export const usePayoutsData = () => {
  return useAppSelector(selector, shallowEqual);
};
```

### 6.3 Local State vs Redux State

**✅ Guidelines:**

```typescript
// Use local state for:
// - UI state (modals, dropdowns, form inputs)
// - Component-specific temporary data
const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);
const [searchTerm, setSearchTerm] = useState('');

// Use Redux state for:
// - Global application state
// - Data shared across multiple components
// - Data that needs to persist across routes
const user = useAppSelector((state) => state.app.user);
```

