## 11. Performance Optimization

### 11.1 Memoization

**✅ Do:**

```typescript
// Memoize expensive calculations
const expensiveValue = useMemo(() => {
  return complexCalculation(data);
}, [data]);

// Memoize callbacks to prevent re-renders
const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
  doSomething(value);
}, [value]);

// Memoize components
const MemoizedComponent = memo(({ data }: Props) => {
  return <div>{data.value}</div>;
});
```

### 11.2 Lazy Loading

**✅ Do:**

```typescript
import lazyLoadWithRetry from 'modules/lazyLoadWithRetry';
import Loader from 'views/xtra/Loader/Loader';

const PayoutsPage = lazyLoadWithRetry(
  () => import('./PayoutsPage' /* webpackChunkName: "payouts-page" */),
);

const App = () => (
  <Suspense fallback={<Loader />}>
    <PayoutsPage />
  </Suspense>
);
```

### 11.3 Avoid Unnecessary Re-renders

**❌ Don't:**

```typescript
// Creating new objects/arrays in render
const MyComponent = () => {
  return <ChildComponent config={{ value: 1 }} />; // New object every render
};

// Inline function definitions for callbacks
<Button onClick={() => handleClick(id)}>Click</Button>;
```

**✅ Do:**

```typescript
// Memoize objects
const config = useMemo(() => ({ value: 1 }), []);
<ChildComponent config={config} />;

// Use useCallback for handlers
const handleButtonClick = useCallback(() => {
  handleClick(id);
}, [id]);
<Button onClick={handleButtonClick}>Click</Button>;
```

