## Quick Reference Checklist

### Before Committing New Code:

- [ ] Component follows directory structure (index.tsx, types.ts, constants.ts, utils.ts, **tests**/)
- [ ] Code organized into separate files (types, constants, utils separate from component logic)
- [ ] No `React.FC` usage
- [ ] No `any` or `unknown` types (unless unavoidable with proper guards)
- [ ] No inline type assertions
- [ ] No class components
- [ ] No HOC compose pattern (use hooks instead)
- [ ] Named exports used (or default for pages)
- [ ] Props destructured in function parameters
- [ ] Early returns used to reduce nesting
- [ ] Blade components used exclusively
- [ ] Blade spacing tokens used (spacing.X)
- [ ] Analytics attributes added (`data-analytics-name`)
- [ ] Tests added with proper coverage
- [ ] Analytics calls tested (if applicable)
- [ ] TypeScript compiles without errors (`yarn tsc --noEmit`)
- [ ] No ESLint errors (`yarn lint`)
- [ ] Build passes (`yarn build`)
- [ ] Error handling with Sentry integration
- [ ] Proper import organization

### Common Code Smells to Avoid:

❌ Using `React.FC`
❌ Using `any` or `unknown` without type guards
❌ Inline type assertions
❌ Class components
❌ HOC compose pattern
❌ Custom UI components instead of Blade
❌ Hardcoded styling instead of Blade tokens
❌ Missing analytics attributes
❌ Untested analytics calls
❌ Missing error handling
❌ Inconsistent file structure
❌ Everything in one file (types, constants, utils mixed with component)
❌ Not destructuring props in parameters
❌ Deep nesting instead of early returns
❌ Default exports everywhere (prefer named)
❌ Massive components (>300 lines)
❌ Complex logic in JSX
❌ Inline functions in render

